      • getScanException

        public Throwable getScanException(String source)
        Returns the exception associated with given searched path. If the given path was not scanned as part of this path or if it was scanned and resolved successfully, this will return null.
        Parameters:
        source - a path that is the source of an exception
        Returns:
        the exception thrown while trying to scan or resolve the given path or null if no exception was thrown or the given name was never scanned
        See Also:
        getScanExceptionSources()

      • getAllScanExceptions

        public Collection<Throwable> getAllScanExceptions()
        Returns all exceptions encountered while trying to scan and resolve classes. This may include any I/O exception encountered while reading from this path. It will also include any exceptions thrown while trying to scan and resolve individual classes in this path.
        Returns:
        all exceptions encountered while trying to scan and resolve classes
        See Also:
        getScanExceptionSources(), getScanException(String)

      • getScanExceptionSources

        public Set<String> getScanExceptionSources()
        Returns the set of paths that were found in this path but could not be scanned or resolved. The cause of failure can be queried using getScanException(String).
        Returns:
        the set of paths that were found in this path but could not be scanned or resolved
